reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2020
reviews.name: Justin
reviews.title: Seems good but alternatives of similar quality are significantly cheaper
reviews.review: I upgraded from a 3rd gen i5 to this product.Looking back, I wish I would have taken a closer look at AMD's lineup of products.Based on the research I have done, it seems that they have processors that will give you nearly identical single threaded performance.Many of their processors also have more throughput.You can get all of this for about half the price.So, you can go with this product for an insignificant gain in in single threaded performance.But you are going to have to pay about double for it.I'm not convinced it was worth it.
